Scholar Author Citations â€‹

ðŸŸ¢ Passed TestðŸš¨ Strict Anti-crawling

ðŸ‘¨â€ðŸ’» Author: @KellyHwong @const7

ðŸ’¡ Example: https://rsshub.app/google/citations/mlmE4JMAAAAJ

ðŸ›Žï¸ Route: /google/citations/:id

ðŸ”— Parameters:

  • id
    • Required
    • Description: N

ðŸ™ Source Code: /google/citations.ts

The parameter id in the route is the id in the URL of the user's Google Scholar reference page, for example https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=mlmE4JMAAAAJ to mlmE4JMAAAAJ.

Query parameters are also supported here, for example https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=mlmE4JMAAAAJ&sortby=pubdate to mlmE4JMAAAAJ&sortby=pubdate. Please make sure that the user id (mlmE4JMAAAAJ in this case) should be the first parameter in the query string.

Scholar Keywords Monitoring â€‹

ðŸŸ¢ Passed TestðŸš¨ Strict Anti-crawling

ðŸ‘¨â€ðŸ’» Author: @HenryQW

ðŸ’¡ Example: https://rsshub.app/google/scholar/data+visualization

ðŸ›Žï¸ Route: /google/scholar/:query

ðŸ”— Parameters:

  • query
    • Required
    • Description: query statement which supportsã€ŒBasicã€andã€ŒAdvancedã€modes

ðŸ™ Source Code: /google/scholar.ts

WARNING

Google Scholar has strict anti-crawling mechanism implemented, the demo below doesn't guarantee availability. Please deploy your own instance as it might increase the stability.

  1. Basic mode, sample query is the keywords desired, eg.ã€Œdata visualizationã€, https://rsshub.app/google/scholar/data+visualization.

  2. Advanced mode, visit Google Scholar, click the top left corner and selectã€ŒAdvanced Searchã€, fill in your conditions and submit the search. The URL should look like this: https://scholar.google.com/scholar?as_q=data+visualization&as_epq=&as_oq=&as_eq=&as_occt=any&as_sauthors=&as_publication=&as_ylo=2018&as_yhi=&hl=en&as_sdt=0%2C5, copy everything after https://scholar.google.com/scholar? from the URL and use it as the query for this route. The complete URL for the above example should look like this: https://rsshub.app/google/scholar/as_q=data+visualization&as_epq=&as_oq=&as_eq=&as_occt=any&as_sauthors=&as_publication=&as_ylo=2018&as_yhi=&hl=en&as_sdt=0%2C5.
